<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by cjd on 07-30-2001 01:31 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Duh, there are a few thousand web pages that list all quests.  But they don't tell ya exactly how much exp you get for them, like we can here with SEQ.

For instance, working from memory (haven't sat down and did the quests in a while), the rabid wolf quests give about 4000 exp points.  Considiring you get about 1500 for killing the wolf, that's an extra 2+ kills for free.

The GLS quest (when you're in appropriate level range) is about 7500 exp points per try; the equivilent of about 1 extra kill.

Many of the quests I've done have server-side level limits.  As you advance, you get more exp points until some peak, then it quickly diminishes.  I suppose it's their attempt to prevent level 1's from doing something like the Burning Rapier and making several levels in one shot.

Speaking of the BR quest, after pondering about it since the last post, I believe the part of killing Lynada and turning in her purse was the quickest to one of the big exp chunks.  My rogue didn't need to do any faction building, but I don't know (yet) if there is anything to prevent other classes from doing it.  Of course the downside is Lynada is like a 4 or 8 hour spawn, so no power-levelling here, but it may be a nice bit of exp if you just are near SolA, first time logging on for the day, etc.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
